<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb89592d0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s6125"><num value="6125">§ 6125.</num><heading> Flexible schedules; time-recording devices</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s6106">section 6106 of this title</ref>, the Office of Personnel Management or any agency may use recording clocks as part of programs under <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s6122">section 6122 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb89592d1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/97/221/s2/a/2">Pub. L. 97–221, § 2(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1982-07-23">July 23, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/229">96 Stat. 229</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
